claims:
8. The method according to claim 1, further comprising:
applying an etch stop layer over the low-k dielectric film and over metal contacts in between the exposed dielectric locations;
depositing a gap-filling, low-k dielectric over the etch stop layer such that the gap-filling, low-k dielectric fills the gaps in the low-k dielectric film;
covering the gap-filling, low-k dielectric with a hard mask;
pattering the hard mask, the gap-filling, low-k dielectric, and the etch stop layer such that at least one opening is created towards the metal contacts; and
applying a metallization layer resulting in at least one via in contact with at least one of the metal contacts.
